<t>CREATE TABLE remote_teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, team_leader VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE projects ( project_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, project_name STRING, team_id UUID REFERENCES teams.team_id )</t><s>SELECT * FROM tasks</s>

CREATE TABLE tasks ( task_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, task_name STRING, assignee UUID REFERENCES employees.id, status STRING )

CREATE TABLE teams ( team_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, team_name STRING, team_lead UUID REFERENCES employees.id )</t><s>select task_name from tasks where assignee = '345678'</s>

CREATE TABLE projects ( project_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, project_name STRING, team_id UUID REFERENCES teams.team_id )

CREATE TABLE tasks ( task_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, task_name STRING, assignee UUID REFERENCES employees.id, status STRING )</t><s>select * from teams order by team_name desc</s>

CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name STRING, team_lead INT, team_members ARRAY<INT>)

CREATE TABLE projects (project_id INT PRIMARY KEY, project_name STRING, project_manager INT, team_assigned INT)</t><s>SELECT * FROM meetings WHERE ARRAY_CONTAINS(meeting_attendees, 4)</s>

CREATE TABLE teams (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY, team_name STRING, team_lead INT, team_members ARRAY<INT>)

CREATE TABLE tasks (task_id INT PRIMARY KEY, task_name STRING, task_description STRING, task_assignee INT)

CREATE TABLE meetings (meeting_id INT PRIMARY KEY, meeting_topic STRING, meeting_date DATE, meeting_attendees ARRAY<INT>)</t><s>SELECT task_description FROM tasks WHERE task_id=8</s>

CREATE TABLE tasks (task_id INT PRIMARY KEY, task_name STRING, task_description STRING, task_assignee INT)
